   International Technology Pact
</HL>
<DATE>
07/31/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   ITX
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   TORRANCE, Calif. -- International Technology Corp. said it
signed a definitive agreement with U.S. Testing Co. to
acquire for cash the assets of U.S. Testing's analytical
laboratory located in Richland, Wash.
   Terms were not disclosed.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The acquisition, which is subject to certain conditions,
including the completion of an environmental audit and
survey, is expected to close in mid-August, International
Technology said.
   U.S. Testing, a Hoboken, N.J.-based environmental-testing
concern, is a unit of SGS North America, a subsidiary of SGS
S.A., Geneva, Switzerland.
   The Richland laboratory performs analytical testing of
hazardous nuclear, chemical, and mixed-waste substances.
   International Technology is an environmental management
company providing services to government and industry.
